{"parentUuid":"c200d474-30cc-49b1-90c3-ee90393842dd","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/ryan/formal-conjectures","sessionId":"59b7283f-1621-48a8-aa4c-bfdcf776f20b","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"ai-erdos-7","agentId":"abc27ea8fe0893a79","slug":"dreamy-toasting-token","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01X78YL8YA9TG3q6vuwvRjAs","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/-\n     2→Copyright 2026 The Formal Conjectures Authors.\n     3→\n     4→Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→\n     8→    https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→\n    10→Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→limitations under the License.\n    15→-/\n    16→\n    17→import FormalConjectures.Util.ProblemImports\n    18→\n    19→/-!\n    20→# Erdős Problem 892\n    21→\n    22→*Reference:* [erdosproblems.com/892](https://www.erdosproblems.com/892)\n    23→\n    24→Is there a necessary and sufficient condition for a sequence of integers\n    25→$b_1 < b_2 < \\cdots$ that ensures there exists a primitive sequence\n    26→$a_1 < a_2 < \\cdots$ (i.e. no element divides another) with $a_n \\ll b_n$\n    27→for all $n$?\n    28→\n    29→[ESS68] Erdős, P., Sárközy, A., and Szemerédi, E.\n    30→\n    31→[Er98] Erdős, P.\n    32→-/\n    33→\n    34→namespace Erdos892\n    35→\n    36→/-- A sequence of natural numbers is *primitive* if no element divides any other. -/\n    37→def IsPrimitiveSeq (a : ℕ → ℕ) : Prop :=\n    38→  ∀ i j, i ≠ j → ¬(a i ∣ a j)\n    39→\n    40→/--\n    41→Erdős Problem 892 (particular case) [Er98]:\n    42→\n    43→If $b : \\mathbb{N} \\to \\mathbb{N}$ is a strictly increasing sequence of positive integers such that\n    44→$\\gcd(b_i, b_j) \\neq b_k$ for all pairwise distinct $i, j, k$ (no non-trivial GCD solutions),\n    45→then there exists a strictly increasing primitive sequence $a : \\mathbb{N} \\to \\mathbb{N}$ with\n    46→$a_n \\ll b_n$ (i.e. there exists $C$ such that $a_n \\leq C \\cdot b_n$ for all $n$).\n    47→-/\n    48→@[category research open, AMS 11]\n    49→theorem erdos_892\n    50→    (b : ℕ → ℕ)\n    51→    (hb_pos : ∀ n, 0 < b n)\n    52→    (hb_mono : StrictMono b)\n    53→    (hb_gcd : ∀ i j k, i ≠ j → i ≠ k → j ≠ k →\n    54→      Nat.gcd (b i) (b j) ≠ b k) :\n    55→    ∃ (a : ℕ → ℕ) (C : ℕ),\n    56→      0 < C ∧\n    57→      StrictMono a ∧\n    58→      IsPrimitiveSeq a ∧\n    59→      ∀ n, a n ≤ C * b n := by\n    60→  sorry\n    61→\n    62→/--\n    63→Erdős Problem 892 (general form) [ESS68] [Er98]:\n    64→\n    65→Characterize which strictly increasing sequences of positive integers $b_1 < b_2 < \\cdots$ have the\n    66→property that there exists a primitive sequence $a_1 < a_2 < \\cdots$ with $a_n \\ll b_n$.\n    67→-/\n    68→@[category research open, AMS 11]\n    69→theorem erdos_892.variants.general :\n    70→    {b : ℕ → ℕ | (∀ n, 0 < b n) ∧ StrictMono b ∧\n    71→      ∃ (a : ℕ → ℕ) (C : ℕ), 0 < C ∧ StrictMono a ∧ IsPrimitiveSeq a ∧\n    72→        ∀ n, a n ≤ C * b n} = answer(sorry) := by\n    73→  sorry\n    74→\n    75→end Erdos892\n    76→"}]},"uuid":"85d8c4fd-937e-412f-8551-46771e2cfa74","timestamp":"2026-03-11T05:20:24.266Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"c200d474-30cc-49b1-90c3-ee90393842dd"}
{"parentUuid":"85d8c4fd-937e-412f-8551-46771e2cfa74","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/ryan/formal-conjectures","sessionId":"59b7283f-1621-48a8-aa4c-bfdcf776f20b","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"ai-erdos-7","agentId":"abc27ea8fe0893a79","slug":"dreamy-toasting-token","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_013FbAbzGJ9LFVArv3Pewe2W","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Found it! Here is the complete information for Erdos Problem 892:\n\n**File Path:** `/home/ryan/formal-conjectures/FormalConjectures/ErdosProblems/892.lean`\n\n**File Contents:**\n\nThe file contains a Lean formalization of Erdős Problem 892, which asks for a necessary and sufficient condition for sequences of integers that ensures the existence of primitive sequences with bounded growth.\n\nKey definitions and theorems in the file:\n\n1. **IsPrimitiveSeq**: A definition stating that a sequence is primitive if no element divides any other.\n\n2. **erdos_892** (particular case): A theorem stating that if b is a strictly increasing sequence of positive integers with the property that gcd(b_i, b_j) ≠ b_k for all pairwise distinct indices, then there exists a strictly increasing primitive sequence a with a_n ≪ b_n (bounded by some constant C times b_n).\n\n3. **erdos_892.variants.general** (general form): A theorem characterizing which strictly increasing sequences of positive integers have the property that there exists a primitive sequence with bounded growth relative to them.\n\nBoth theorems are marked as open research problems (indicated by the `@[category research open, AMS 11]` attribute) and currently contain `sorry` placeholders, indicating they remain unproven."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1457,"cache_read_input_tokens":19716,"output_tokens":312,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation"